SUMMARY:Survivalist Series: Introduction to Cold Exposure
DESCRIPTION:Wilderness Union Toronto - Outdoor Adventure and Hiking Club\n
 **Please note the only way to register for this adventure is on [our websi
 te.](https://www.wildernessunion.com/adventures/intro-cold-exposure)**\n\n
 **Learning how to embrace the cold and manage its risks is key to enjoying
  the Canadian outdoors all year ‘round.**\n\nIn this adventure\, we will
  combine hiking in a rugged winter landscape with skill-building challenge
 s\, teaching you how to thrive in cold conditions. You will learn:\n\n* Ho
 w to dress and act to stay warm and healthy during outdoor activities in c
 old conditions\n* The basics of preventing\, recognizing\, and responding 
 to hypothermia and frostbite\n* How to recognize hazardous ice and snow\, 
 and what to do in case of accidental immersion in frozen water\n* Optional
 ly (and weather/conditions permitting)\, you could take on the challenge o
 f a real cold plunge in a frozen lake\, with expert guidance and safety pl
 anning.\n\nThis course is led by Sarah\, our amazing guide and medical doc
 tor who has experience as a first responder in remote environments and exp
 ertise in simulation-based teaching of emergency skills.\n\n**Interested i
 n joining this year’s Epics? Completing this and other relevant courses 
 will support your approval process for advanced adventures.**\n\n**Include
 d:** Essential cold-weather items to add to your personal first aid kit\, 
 including a hypothermia blanket and ‘Cold Card’.\n\n**Who It’s For**
 : Anyone who wants to spend time outdoors with confidence in all four seas
 ons! No previous first aid experience is required. For those with prior wi
 lderness first aid training\, or other healthcare experience\, this worksh
 op is an opportunity to gain valuable extra repetitions honing your skills
  in a realistic outdoor environment.\n\n**About this series:** The Surviva
 list Series is an expert-led set of courses designed to develop applicable
  and life-saving skills in the outdoors. Keep your eyes peeled for more co
 urses on many other topics as they become available.\n\n**Due to limited p
 arking at the course location\, WU transport is strongly recommended. We c
 annot guarantee safe parking for your vehicle.**\n\n**Highlights**\n**Surv
 ivalist Skills Training:** Develop essential skills to survive and thrive 
 in the wild.\n**Expert Instructors:** Our amazing expert guides will teach
  you everything you need to know in a safe and fun way.\n**Cold Exposure K
 it Included:** Each participant will get a ‘cold card’ and an emergenc
 y blanket to add to their medical kits.\n\n**Event cost: $90+HST - optiona
 l transport available.**\n**Register [here.](https://www.wildernessunion.c
 om/adventures/intro-cold-exposure)**\n\n**About Wilderness Union**\nWilder
 ness Union is deliberate about building an outdoors community that connect
 s you to the life-changing magic of the outdoors and helps you find your p
 eople.\n\nMembers range from 20-40 years old. The group is a mix of GTA lo
 cals and newcomers to Toronto from within Canada and abroad.\n\nAttendance
  numbers on Meetup don't reflect our actual event attendance - we typicall
 y have 15-20 community members at each event. Large enough that there's so
 meone new to meet but small enough that it's not overwhelming!\n\n***Learn
  more at our website [www.wildernessunion.com](https://www.wildernessunion
 .com/)***
